title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: that a very thrall should out-do him in the hunting of deer: so he
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: snow-drift.

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: appointed to Gothland at the bidding of King Siggeir, and put off from
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: But that same night came Signy and called her father and brothers to a
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: privy talk, and told them what she deemed King Siggeir was minded to do,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: and how that he had drawn together an army no man may meet. "And," says
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: she, "he is minded to do guilefully by you; wherefore I bid you get
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: ye gone back again to your own land, and gather together the mightiest
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: power ye may, and then come back hither and avenge you; neither go ye
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: now to your undoing, for ye shall surely fail not to fall by his wiles
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: if ye turn not on him even as I bid you."

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: the wide world.

text: Now Sigurd's foster-father was hight Regin, the son of Hreidmar; he
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: if he knew how much wealth his father had owned, and who had the ward
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

author: NA

text: therewith, for better they wot how to guard it than I do."

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: Another time came Regin to talk to Sigurd, and said--

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "A marvellous thing truly that thou must needs be a horse-boy to the
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: kings, and go about like a running knave."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "Nay," said Sigurd, "it is not so, for in all things I have my will, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: whatso thing I desire is granted me with good will."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "Well, then," said Regin, "ask for a horse of them."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "Yea," quoth Sigurd, "and that shall I have, whenso I have need
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: thereof."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Thereafter Sigurd went to the king, and the king said--
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "What wilt thou have of us?"
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Then said Sigurd, "I would even a horse of thee for my disport."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Then said the king, "Choose for thyself a horse, and whatso thing else
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: thou desirest among my matters."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: So the next day went Sigurd to the wood, and met on the way an old man,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: long-bearded, that he knew not, who asked him whither away.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Sigurd said, "I am minded to choose me a horse; come thou, and counsel
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: me thereon."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "Well then," said he, "go we and drive them to the river which is called
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Busil-tarn."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: They did so, and drave the horses down into the deeps of the river, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: all swam back to land but one horse; and that horse Sigurd chose for
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: himself; grey he was of hue, and young of years, great of growth, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: fair to look on, nor had any man yet crossed his back.

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Then spake the grey-beard, "From Sleipnir's kin is this horse come, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: Now yet again spake Regin to Sigurd, and said--

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: run here and there like a churl's son; but I can tell thee where there
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: as of other lingworms, (1) and an over great tale men make of it; and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: "The tale begins," said Regin. "Hreidmar was my father's name, a mighty
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: man and a wealthy: and his first son was named Fafnir, his second Otter,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: and I was the third, and the least of them all both for prowess and good
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: conditions, but I was cunning to work in iron, and silver, and gold,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: whereof I could make matters that availed somewhat. Other skill my
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: brother Otter followed, and had another nature withal, for he was a
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: great fisher, and above other men herein; in that he had the likeness of
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: an otter by day, and dwelt ever in the river, and bare fish to bank
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: in his mouth, and his prey would he ever bring to our father, and that
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: availed him much: for the most part he kept him in his otter-gear, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: then he would come home, and eat alone, and slumbering, for on the
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: dry land he might see naught. But Fafnir was by far the greatest and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: grimmest, and would have all things about called his.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "Now," says Regin, "there was a dwarf called Andvari, who ever abode in
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: that force, (1) which was called Andvari's force, in the likeness of a
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: pike, and got meat for himself, for many fish there were in the force;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: now Otter, my brother, was ever wont to enter into the force, and bring
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: fish aland, and lay them one by one on the bank. And so it befell that
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Odin, Loki, and Hoenir, as they went their ways, came to Andvari's
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: force, and Otter had taken a salmon, and ate it slumbering upon the
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: river bank; then Loki took a stone and cast it at Otter, so that he gat
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: his death thereby; the gods were well content with their prey, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: fell to flaying off the otter's skin; and in the evening they came to
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: hands on them, and doomed them to such ransom, as that they should fill
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: they sent Loki to gather gold together for them; he came to Ran, (2)
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: and got her net, and went therewith to Andvari's force, and cast the net
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: before the pike, and the pike ran into the net and was taken. Then said
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "'What fish of all fishes,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: And find me the wan waters flame.'
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: He answered--
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: "'Andvari folk call me,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Call Oinn my father,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Over many a force have I fared;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: For a Norn of ill-luck,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: This life on me lay
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Through wet ways ever to wade.'
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: "To three men was I wedded, and first to Sigurd Fafnir's-bane, and he

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Then was I given to King Atli, and so fell was my heart toward him that
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: CHAPTER XLIII. The Latter End of all the Kin of the Giukings.

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Now telleth the tale concerning the sons of Gudrun, that she had arrayed
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: their war-raiment in such wise, that no steel would bite thereon; and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: she bade them play not with stones or other heavy matters, for that it
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: would be to their scathe if they did so.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: And now, as they went on their way, they met Erp, their brother, and
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: asked him in what wise he would help them.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: He answered, "Even as hand helps hand, or foot helps foot."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: But that they deemed naught at all, and slew him there and then. Then
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: thrust down his hand to steady himself, and spake therewith--
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: not hand been to steady me."
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: so stood, and spake--
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: But there came thereto a certain man, old of aspect and one-eyed, (1)
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: Now this is my first counsel,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: That thou with thy kin
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Be guiltless, guileless ever,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Nor hasty of wrath,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Despite of wrong done--
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Unto the dead good that doeth.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Lo the second counsel,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: That oath thou swearest never,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: But trusty oath and true:
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Grim tormenting
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Gripes troth-breakers;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Cursed wretch is the wolf of vows.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: This is my third rede,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: That thou at the Thing
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Deal not with the fools of folk;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: For unwise man
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: From mouth lets fall
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Worser word than well he wotteth.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Yet hard it is
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: That holding of peace
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: When men shall deem thee dastard,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Or deem the lie said soothly;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: But woeful is home-witness,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Unless right good thou gettest it.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Ah, on another day
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Drive the life from out him,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: And pay the liar back for his lying.
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Now behold the fourth rede:
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: If ill witch thee bideth,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Woe-begatting by the way,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Good going further
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Rather than guesting,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Though thick night be on thee.

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Far-seeing eyes
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Need all sons of men
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Who wend in wrath to war;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: For baleful women
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Bide oft by the highway,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Swords and hearts to soften.

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

text: And now the fifth rede:
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Brides on the bench abiding,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Let not love's silver
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Rule over thy sleeping;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Amid ale-words and ill-words,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Have brought unto men
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: And to some weary bale;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: For the seventh, I rede thee,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: If strife thou raisest
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: With a man right high of heart,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Better fight a-field
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Than burn in the fire
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Within thine hall fair to behold.

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: The eighth rede that I give thee:
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Unto all ill look thou,
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: And hold thine heart from all beguiling;
title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
author: NA

text: Urge them not unto unmeet pleasure.

author: NA

title: The Story of the Volsungs (Volsunga Saga); with Excerpts from the Poetic Edda
